# CLS Cognitive Loop — CLAUDE.md Template
# Copy to your project root as CLAUDE.md and fill in {PLACEHOLDER} values.
# This template encodes the 6-step cognitive cycle as behavioral instructions.

# P0 — Cognitive Core Loop
Every task passes through 6 mandatory steps:
1. Situational Awareness — read context + trajectory, match keywords
2. Task Execution — scope, pre-flight, execute, cleanup
3. Associative Learning — match new knowledge against known patterns
4. Abstract Generalization — decontextualize into transferable patterns
5. Context Persistence — write checkpoint to disk
6. Trajectory Update — record delta-Q, delta-P; close loop back to step 1

# P0 — Fact Anchoring Protocol
Every claim must reference file path + field value. No reference = not substantiated.

# P0 — Dual-AI Gate
- Generator: {GENERATOR_MODEL} — creates designs, writes code
- Evaluator: {EVALUATOR_MODEL} — independently verifies all outputs
- P(system error) ~ P(Generator err) x P(Evaluator err)

# P0 — Fuse Board
6 independent fuses (pure stdlib):
- WRITE_PROTECT: block unauthorized writes to core files
- RECURSION_LIMIT: max depth {MAX_RECURSION_DEPTH}
- TOKEN_BUDGET: {SESSION_TOKEN_BUDGET} session / {DAILY_TOKEN_BUDGET} daily
- PARALLEL_CAP: max {MAX_PARALLEL_TASKS} concurrent
- CHECKPOINT_REQUIRED: every {CHECKPOINT_INTERVAL_SEC}s

